broadsoft.name: broadsoft

revisions.description: Added new counters for Release 8. The BroadWorks counters were also changed from read-only to read-write. Group based service counter tables were introduced.
Added POP3 and SMTP performance measurement . Added instantConferencing module and the following performance measurements: bwICGroupPortLimitExceeded bwICNumAttempts bwICInvalidPasscode
Reintroduce instant conferencing statistics as service performance measurements.
Added POP3 and SMTP performance measurement .

bwMGCPStatsDialToneDelay.name: bwMGCPStatsDialToneDelay
bwMGCPStatsDialToneDelay.description: This gauge measures the average time (in milliseconds) between receipt of NTFY indicating off-hook and transmission of RQNT indicating dial-tone and request for digits

bwMGCPStatsMinDialToneDelay.name: bwMGCPStatsMinDialToneDelay
bwMGCPStatsMinDialToneDelay.description: This measures the shortest MGCP dial-tone delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared

bwMGCPStatsMaxDialToneDelay.name: bwMGCPStatsMaxDialToneDelay
bwMGCPStatsMaxDialToneDelay.description: This measures the longest MGCP dial-tone delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared

bwMGCPStatsSetupSignalDelay.name: bwMGCPStatsSetupSignalDelay
bwMGCPStatsSetupSignalDelay.description: This gauge is applicable to MGCP originated calls. It measures the average time (in milliseconds) it takes between the receipt of a NTFY message with digits dialed for the origination of a new call and the transmission of an INVITE (Sip terminator), RQNT (MGCP terminator with in-band ringback), or CRCX (MGCP terminator without in-band ringback) to the primary device of the original called party (in the case of intra-group call) or to the network element of the original called party (in the case of a call to the PSTN). Delays incurred by a dip to the Network Server are removed from the measurement. This measurement is intended to reflect internal queuing, scheduling, and processing delays. The same clarifications as for bwSipStatsSetupSignalDelay apply to bwMGCPStatsSetupSignalDelay

bwMGCPStatsMinSetupSignalDelay.name: bwMGCPStatsMinSetupSignalDelay
bwMGCPStatsMinSetupSignalDelay.description: This measures the shortest MGCP setup-signal delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared

bwMGCPStatsMaxSetupSignalDelay.name: bwMGCPStatsMaxSetupSignalDelay
bwMGCPStatsMaxSetupSignalDelay.description: This measures the shortest MGCP setup-signal delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared

bwMGCPStatsAnswerSignalDelay.name: bwMGCPStatsAnswerSignalDelay
bwMGCPStatsAnswerSignalDelay.description: This gauge measures the average time (in milliseconds) between the receipt of a 200 OK message indicating answer or a NTFY off-hook indicating answer and the transmission of a MDCX indicating answer to the originator. This measurement is intended to reflect internal queuing, scheduling, and processing delays. This gauge is applicable to only the MGCP originated calls for which the setup-signal delay is measured. Answer signal delay is not measured when the call has been forwarded, redirected, or when the call has encountered route advancing.

bwMGCPStatsMinAnswerSignalDelay.name: bwMGCPStatsMinAnswerSignalDelay
bwMGCPStatsMinAnswerSignalDelay.description: This measures the shortest MGCP answer-signal delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared.

bwMGCPStatsMaxAnswerSignalDelay.name: bwMGCPStatsMaxAnswerSignalDelay
bwMGCPStatsMaxAnswerSignalDelay.description: This measures the longest MGCP answer-signal delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared.

bwMGCPStatsMessageRetryPercentage.name: bwMGCPStatsMessageRetryPercentage
bwMGCPStatsMessageRetryPercentage.description: This gauge measures the percentage of MGCP requests sent due to retry. Of up to the last 100 requests sent, this gauge calculates the percentage sent due to retransmission (i.e. - gauge = MGCP request retransmissions / (MGCP request initial transmissions + MGCP request retransmissions).

bwMCPCommandsTransmitted.name: bwMCPCommandsTransmitted
bwMCPCommandsTransmitted.description: Incremented each time an MCP command is transmitted. This object is obsolete. The MCP interface is no longer used by the Application Server.

bwMCPCommandsRetransmitted.name: bwMCPCommandsRetransmitted
bwMCPCommandsRetransmitted.description: Incremented each time an MCP command is re-transmitted. This object is obsolete. The MCP interface is no longer used by the Application Server.

bwMCPNotificationsReceived.name: bwMCPNotificationsReceived
bwMCPNotificationsReceived.description: Incremented each time an MCP notification is received This object is obsolete. The MCP interface is no longer used by the Application Server.

bwMCPResourceAllocAttempts.name: bwMCPResourceAllocAttempts
bwMCPResourceAllocAttempts.description: A resource allocation request is defined as an application layer request for a Media Server resource request (i.e. IVR connection, bridge). This counter is incremented by the MCP protocol layer upon receipt of the resource allocation request from the application layer (i.e. prior transmission of any MCP resource allocation Command) This object is obsolete. The MCP interface is no longer used by the Application Server.

bwMCPResourceAllocFailures.name: bwMCPResourceAllocFailures
bwMCPResourceAllocFailures.description: A resource allocation request is defined as an application layer request for a Media Server resource request (i.e.  IVR connection, bridge). This counter is incremented by the MCP protocol layer when resource allocation Commands have been transmitted toward all available Media Servers and no resource on any Media Server was allocated. This object is obsolete. The MCP interface is no longer used by the Application Server.

bwIMSSuccessfulConnectionAttempts.name: bwIMSSuccessfulConnectionAttempts
bwIMSSuccessfulConnectionAttempts.description: This counter reflects the number of successful connection to incoming mail server.

bwIMSUnsuccessfulConnectionAttempts.name: bwIMSUnsuccessfulConnectionAttempts
bwIMSUnsuccessfulConnectionAttempts.description: This counter reflects the total number of unsuccessful connection to incoming mail server.

bwIMSSuccessfulDownLoadAttempts.name: bwIMSSuccessfulDownLoadAttempts
bwIMSSuccessfulDownLoadAttempts.description: This counter reflects the number of messages downloaded from incoming mail server.

bwIMSUnsuccessfulDownLoadAttempts.name: bwIMSUnsuccessfulDownLoadAttempts
bwIMSUnsuccessfulDownLoadAttempts.description: This counter reflects the number of unsuccessful message download attempted on incoming mail server.

bwIMSMaxSessions.name: bwIMSMaxSessions
bwIMSMaxSessions.description: Maximum number of incoming mail server sessions simultaneously active since the system was started. A session is defined as a complete dialog between the execution server and the incoming mail server, and includes elements such as mailbox information requests, message download requests, and idle time.

bwIMSAvgSessions.name: bwIMSAvgSessions
bwIMSAvgSessions.description: Average number of incoming mail server sessions simultaneously active, based on a rolling average over the last 100 sessions. Each data point is computed right after the creation of a session. A session is defined as a complete dialog between the execution server and the incoming mail server, and includes elements such as mailbox information requests, message download requests, and idle time.

bwIMSMaxThreads.name: bwIMSMaxThreads
bwIMSMaxThreads.description: Maximum number of incoming mail server threads simultaneously active since the system was started. IMS threads are used when a session actively communicates with an IMS, and waits for a response. A session does not use an IMS thread while it is idle, e.g. prompting or waiting for user input.

bwIMSAvgThreads.name: bwIMSAvgThreads
bwIMSAvgThreads.description: Average number of incoming mail server threads simultaneously active, based on a rolling average over the last 100 sessions. Each data point is computed right after the creation of a session. IMS threads are used when a session actively communicates with an IMS, and waits for a response. A session does not use an IMS thread while it is idle, e.g. prompting or waiting for user input.

bwIMSMaxServiceTime.name: bwIMSMaxServiceTime
bwIMSMaxServiceTime.description: Maximum time in milliseconds required to process an incoming mail server request, since the system was started. This service time includes any queuing time if applicable. This time also includes the time required by the IMS to respond to a request such as a mailbox information request, or a message download request.

bwIMSAvgServiceTime.name: bwIMSAvgServiceTime
bwIMSAvgServiceTime.description: Average time in milliseconds required to process an incoming mail server request, based on a rolling average over the last 100 requests. This service time includes any queuing time if applicable. This time also includes the time required by the IMS to respond to a request such as a mailbox information request, or a message download request.

bwIMSNumKeepAlive.name: bwIMSNumKeepAlive
bwIMSNumKeepAlive.description: Number of times a keep-alive message was sent to an incoming mail server. Such a keep-alive message is sent when an IMS session lasts several minutes.

bwIMSNumDroppedRequests.name: bwIMSNumDroppedRequests
bwIMSNumDroppedRequests.description: Number of incoming mail server requests dropped because the number of IMS threads was too low, and the queue was full. Note that a single session can make several requests to the IMS.

bwCAPStatsAclViolations.name: bwCAPStatsAclViolations

bwCAPStatsRegisterResponsesTable.name: bwCAPStatsRegisterResponsesTable
bwCAPStatsRegisterResponsesTable.description: This table contains counters for the different types of CAP registerResponse messages sent by the system in response to a received CAP registerRequest message. The following are the various types of registerResponse messages and an index value identifying each type: 1 - successful registerResponse, 2 - unsuccessful registerResponse (unknown user id), 3 - unsuccessful registerResponse (incorrect user credentials), 4 - unsuccessful registerResponse (feature unauthorized).

bwCAPStatsCallControlInfosOut.name: bwCAPStatsCallControlInfosOut
bwCAPStatsCallControlInfosOut.description: This counter is incremented whenever a CAP callControlInfo message is sent out by the system

bwCAPStatsRegisterAuthentications.name: bwCAPStatsRegisterAuthentications
bwCAPStatsRegisterAuthentications.description: This counter is incremented whenever the Execution Server receives a registerAuthentication CAP message

bwCAPStatsResponseAuthentications.name: bwCAPStatsResponseAuthentications
bwCAPStatsResponseAuthentications.description: This counter is incremented whenever the Execution Server receives a responseAuthentication CAP message

bwCAPStatsInfoRequests.name: bwCAPStatsInfoRequests
bwCAPStatsInfoRequests.description: This counter is incremented whenever the Execution Server receives a infoRequest CAP message

bwCAPStatsInfoResponses.name: bwCAPStatsInfoResponses
bwCAPStatsInfoResponses.description: This counter is incremented whenever the Execution Server receives a infoResponse CAP message

bwCAPStatsExternalNotifies.name: bwCAPStatsExternalNotifies
bwCAPStatsExternalNotifies.description: This counter is incremented whenever the Execution Server receives a externalNotify CAP message

bwCAPMonitoringUsersRequests.name: bwCAPMonitoringUsersRequests
bwCAPMonitoringUsersRequests.description: The number of monitoringUsersRequest CAP messages received.

bwCAPMonitoringUsersResponses.name: bwCAPMonitoringUsersResponses
bwCAPMonitoringUsersResponses.description: The number of monitoringUsersResponse CAP messages sent.

bwCAPStatsQueueUpdatesOut.name: bwCAPStatsQueueUpdatesOut
bwCAPStatsQueueUpdatesOut.description: This counter reflects the number of CAP queueUpdate messages that have been sent out by the system.

bwCAPStatsQueueActionsIn.name: bwCAPStatsQueueActionsIn
bwCAPStatsQueueActionsIn.description: This counter reflects the number of CAP queueAction messages that have been received by the system.

bwCAPStatsDatagramsIn.name: bwCAPStatsDatagramsIn
bwCAPStatsDatagramsIn.description: This counter reflects the number of CAP datagram commands that have been received by the system.

bwCAPStatsDatagramsOut.name: bwCAPStatsDatagramsOut
bwCAPStatsDatagramsOut.description: This counter reflects the number of CAP datagram commands that have been sent by the system.

bwCAPStatsTotalMsgs.name: bwCAPStatsTotalMsgs
bwCAPStatsTotalMsgs.description: This counter cumulates the total number of CAP messages that have been handled by the system.

bwCAPStatsRegisterResponsesEntry.name: bwCAPStatsRegisterResponsesEntry
bwCAPStatsRegisterResponsesEntry.description: This row contains information on a particular CAP registerResponse type sent out by the system.

bwCAPStatsRegisterResponsesType.name: bwCAPStatsRegisterResponsesType
bwCAPStatsRegisterResponsesType.description: This integer represents a registerResponse type. This is also the index into the table.

bwCAPStatsRegisterResponses.name: bwCAPStatsRegisterResponses
bwCAPStatsRegisterResponses.description: This counter reflects the number of CAP registerResponse messages that have been sent out by the system.

bwSmdiNbOfActiveConnection.name: bwSmdiNbOfActiveConnection
bwSmdiNbOfActiveConnection.description: Counts the total number of currently active Terminal Server SMDI connections.

bwSmdiNbOfOpenedConnection.name: bwSmdiNbOfOpenedConnection
bwSmdiNbOfOpenedConnection.description: This counter gives the total number of SMDI connections that were opened since the last reboot of the system or reset of the PMs.

bwSmdiIncomingMWIActivationRequests.name: bwSmdiIncomingMWIActivationRequests
bwSmdiIncomingMWIActivationRequests.description: This counter reflects the number of SMDI MWI activation requests that were received and processed by the server.

bwSmdiIncomingMWIDesactivationRequests.name: bwSmdiIncomingMWIDesactivationRequests
bwSmdiIncomingMWIDesactivationRequests.description: This counter reflects the number of SMDI MWI desactivation requests that were received and processed by the server.

bwSmdiInvalidRequestsReceived.name: bwSmdiInvalidRequestsReceived
bwSmdiInvalidRequestsReceived.description: This counter reflects the number of invalid SMDI requests.

bwSmdiBlockResponsesSent.name: bwSmdiBlockResponsesSent
bwSmdiBlockResponsesSent.description: This counter reflects the number of SMDI MWI negative acknowledgement with a cause set to BLK.

bwSmdiInvalidResponsesSent.name: bwSmdiInvalidResponsesSent
bwSmdiInvalidResponsesSent.description: This counter reflects the number of SMDI MWI negative acknowledgement with a cause set to INV.

bwSmdiOutgoingMWIActivationRequests.name: bwSmdiOutgoingMWIActivationRequests
bwSmdiOutgoingMWIActivationRequests.description: This counter reflects the number of Number of outgoing SMDI MWI OP message.

bwSmdiOutgoingMWIDeactivationRequests.name: bwSmdiOutgoingMWIDeactivationRequests
bwSmdiOutgoingMWIDeactivationRequests.description: This counter reflects the number of Number of outgoing SMDI MWI RMV message.

bwSmdiBlockResponsesReceived.name: bwSmdiBlockResponsesReceived
bwSmdiBlockResponsesReceived.description: This counter reflects the number of SMDI MWI negative acknowledgement with a cause set to BLK received from a station host, i.e. a Class 5 End Office.

bwSmdiInvalidResponsesReceived.name: bwSmdiInvalidResponsesReceived
bwSmdiInvalidResponsesReceived.description: This counter reflects the number of SMDI MWI negative acknowledgement with a cause set to INV.

bwSMDIMessageDeskMessageSent.name: bwSMDIMessageDeskMessageSent
bwSMDIMessageDeskMessageSent.description: This counter reflects the number of outgoing SMDI MD messages sent by BroadWorks.

bwMediaCommandsTransmitted.name: bwMediaCommandsTransmitted
bwMediaCommandsTransmitted.description: Contains the number of times a media command was transmitted, for the entire Application Server.

bwMediaNotificationsReceived.name: bwMediaNotificationsReceived
bwMediaNotificationsReceived.description: Contains the number of times a media notification was received, for the entire Application Server.

bwMediaResourceAllocAttempts.name: bwMediaResourceAllocAttempts
bwMediaResourceAllocAttempts.description: Contains the number of media resource allocation attempts, for the entire Application Server.

bwMediaResourceAllocFailures.name: bwMediaResourceAllocFailures
bwMediaResourceAllocFailures.description: Contains the number of times a media command was transmitted, for the entire Application Server.

bwWSPStatsServiceRequestsIn.name: bwWSPStatsServiceRequestsIn
bwWSPStatsServiceRequestsIn.description: This counter is incremented whenever a WSP ServiceRequest message is received.

bwWSPStatsServiceActionsOut.name: bwWSPStatsServiceActionsOut
bwWSPStatsServiceActionsOut.description: This counter is incremented whenever a WSP ServiceAction message is transmitted.

bwWSPStatsServiceUpdatesIn.name: bwWSPStatsServiceUpdatesIn
bwWSPStatsServiceUpdatesIn.description: This counter is incremented whenever a WSP ServiceUpdate message is received.

bwWSPStatsServiceAcknowledgementsOut.name: bwWSPStatsServiceAcknowledgementsOut
bwWSPStatsServiceAcknowledgementsOut.description: This counter is incremented whenever a WSP ServiceAcknowledgement message is transmitted.

bwRealtimeAccountingRequestsTransmitted.name: bwRealtimeAccountingRequestsTransmitted
bwRealtimeAccountingRequestsTransmitted.description: Number of new Accounting Requests sent to a Radius Server. Incremented each time a new Accounting Request transmission is first attempted toward a Radius Server.

bwRealtimeAccountingRequestsRetransmitte.name: bwRealtimeAccountingRequestsRetransmitted
bwRealtimeAccountingRequestsRetransmitte.description: Number of Accounting Requests sent to Radius Server(s) due to retransmissions to the same server. Incremented each time an Accounting Request transmission is retransmitted toward an Accounting Radius Server (be it to the same server as the one where the original request was sent, or to the alternate server).

bwRealtimeAccountingRequestsDropped.name: bwRealtimeAccountingRequestsDropped
bwRealtimeAccountingRequestsDropped.description: Number of Accounting Requests that were discarded due to the lack of a responsive Accounting Radius Server. Incremented each time an Accounting Request is dropped, after all transmissions attempts have failed.

bwExternalCallLogsTransmitted.name: bwExternalCallLogsTransmitted
bwExternalCallLogsTransmitted.description: Incremented each time a new external call log transmission is first attempted toward a Call detail server.

bwExternalCallLogsRetransmitted.name: bwExternalCallLogsRetransmitted
bwExternalCallLogsRetransmitted.description: Incremented each time a new external call log transmission is retransmitted towards a Call Detail Radius Server (be it to the same server as the one where the original call log was sent, or to the alternate server).

bwExternalCallLogsDropped.name: bwExternalCallLogsDropped
bwExternalCallLogsDropped.description: Incremented each time a call log is dropped, after all transmissions attempts have failed.

bwExternalCallLogsQueued.name: bwExternalCallLogsQueued
bwExternalCallLogsQueued.description: Incremented each time a call log is written to the AS file-based queue, after all transmissions attempts have failed.

bwExternalCallLogsTransmittedFromQueue.name: bwExternalCallLogsTransmittedFromQueue
bwExternalCallLogsTransmittedFromQueue.description: Incremented on the first attempt to send to the call detail server a call log read from the file based queue.

bwExternalCallLogsRetransmittedFromQueue.name: bwExternalCallLogsRetransmittedFromQueue
bwExternalCallLogsRetransmittedFromQueue.description: Incremented on all attempts but the first one to send to the Call Detail Server a call log read from the file based queue.

bwCommonCommXSStatsTable.name: bwCommonCommXSStatsTable
bwCommonCommXSStatsTable.description: This table contains counters for BCCT for the XS process.

bwCommonCommXSStatsEntry.name: bwCommonCommXSStatsEntry
bwCommonCommXSStatsEntry.description: Definition of the entries for bwCommonCommXSStatsTable.

bwCommonCommXSStatsIndex.name: bwCommonCommXSStatsIndex
bwCommonCommXSStatsIndex.description: This integer represents an index in table bwCommonCommXSStatsTable. The index represents a connection for a specific Host-Interfacece-Protocol combination.

bwCommonCommXSHost.name: bwCommonCommXSHost
bwCommonCommXSHost.description: The address of a host connected to the BroadWorks Common Communication Protocol.

bwCommonCommXSInterface.name: bwCommonCommXSInterface
bwCommonCommXSInterface.description: The IP address of a local interface that a protocol is bound to.

bwCommonCommXSProtocol.name: bwCommonCommXSProtocol
bwCommonCommXSProtocol.description: The name of a BroadWorks Common Communication Protocol client protocol, e.g. OCI or SyncApi.

bwCommonCommXSAcceptedOutboundConnection.name: bwCommonCommXSAcceptedOutboundConnections
bwCommonCommXSAcceptedOutboundConnection.description: This counter is incremented whenever a client in this process connects to the framework to a remote host, using the interface and protocol.

bwCommonCommXSAcceptedInboundConnections.name: bwCommonCommXSAcceptedInboundConnections
bwCommonCommXSAcceptedInboundConnections.description: This counter is incremented whenever a client in this process connects to the framework from a remote host, using the interface and protocol.

bwCommonCommXSRejectedOutboundConnection.name: bwCommonCommXSRejectedOutboundConnections
bwCommonCommXSRejectedOutboundConnection.description: This counter is incremented whenever a client connection request going from this process to a remote host and going through this interface has been rejected for a particular protocol.

bwCommonCommXSRejectedInboundConnections.name: bwCommonCommXSRejectedInboundConnections
bwCommonCommXSRejectedInboundConnections.description: This counter is incremented whenever a client connection request coming to this host and going through this interface has been rejected by the framework for a particular protocol.

bwCommonCommXSOutputMessagesProcessed.name: bwCommonCommXSOutputMessagesProcessed
bwCommonCommXSOutputMessagesProcessed.description: This counter is incremented whenever a message has been sent and processed for this host, interface and protocol.

bwCommonCommXSInputMessagesProcessed.name: bwCommonCommXSInputMessagesProcessed
bwCommonCommXSInputMessagesProcessed.description: This counter is incremented whenever a message has been received and processed for this host, interface and protocol.

bwCommonCommXSOutputCommunicationErrors.name: bwCommonCommXSOutputCommunicationErrors
bwCommonCommXSOutputCommunicationErrors.description: This counter is incremented whenever a message could not be read because the TCP stack returned an error.

bwCommonCommXSInputCommunicationErrors.name: bwCommonCommXSInputCommunicationErrors
bwCommonCommXSInputCommunicationErrors.description: This counter is incremented whenever a message has been sent and processed for this host, interface and protocol.

bwXSMonitoringExecutorTable.name: bwXSMonitoringExecutorTable
bwXSMonitoringExecutorTable.description: This table contains counters for the concurrent framework.

bwXSMonitoringExecutorEntry.name: bwXSMonitoringExecutorEntry
bwXSMonitoringExecutorEntry.description: Definition of the entries for bwXSMonitoringExecutorTable.

bwXSMonitoringExecutorIndex.name: bwXSMonitoringExecutorIndex
bwXSMonitoringExecutorIndex.description: This integer represents an index in table bwXSMonitoringExecutorTable. This is the index to a specific Monitoring Executor name.

bwXSMonitoringExecutorName.name: bwXSMonitoringExecutorName
bwXSMonitoringExecutorName.description: The name of the Monitoring Executor - Names are internally defined at the application level.

bwXSMonitoringExecutorAvgActiveThreads.name: bwXSMonitoringExecutorAvgActiveThreads
bwXSMonitoringExecutorAvgActiveThreads.description: The average number of active threads, rounded up

bwXSMonitoringExecutorTaskQueueSize.name: bwXSMonitoringExecutorTaskQueueSize
bwXSMonitoringExecutorTaskQueueSize.description: Number of tasks in the queue (includes scheduled and recurring tasks)

bwXSMonitoringExecutorLongestTaskMs.name: bwXSMonitoringExecutorLongestTaskMs
bwXSMonitoringExecutorLongestTaskMs.description: Longest completed task execution time in milliseconds

bwXSTcpServersStatsTable.name: bwXSTcpServersStatsTable
bwXSTcpServersStatsTable.description: This table contains counters for TCP underlying framework for the XS process.

bwXSTcpServersStatsEntry.name: bwXSTcpServersStatsEntry
bwXSTcpServersStatsEntry.description: Definition of the entries for bwXSTcpServersStatsTable.

bwXSTcpServersStatsIndex.name: bwXSTcpServersStatsIndex
bwXSTcpServersStatsIndex.description: This integer represents an index in table bwXSTcpServersStatsTable. This is the index to a specific TCP server name.

bwXSTcpServersName.name: bwXSTcpServersName
bwXSTcpServersName.description: The name of TCP server - Names are internally defined at at the application level.

bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsAccepted.name: bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsAccepted
bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsAccepted.description: This counter represents the number of connections accepted by the TCP server.

bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsRefused.name: bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsRefused
bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsRefused.description: This counter represents the number of connections refused by the TCP server.

bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsInitiated.name: bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsInitiated
bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsInitiated.description: This counter represents the number of connections initiated by the TCP server.

bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsClosed.name: bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsClosed
bwXSTcpServersNbConnectionsClosed.description: This counter represents the number of connections closed by the TCP server or remote hosts.

bwXSTcpServersNbBytesSent.name: bwXSTcpServersNbBytesSent
bwXSTcpServersNbBytesSent.description: This counter represents the number of bytes sent by the TCP server.

bwXSTcpServersNbBytesReceived.name: bwXSTcpServersNbBytesReceived
bwXSTcpServersNbBytesReceived.description: This counter represents the number of bytes received by the TCP server.

bwXSTcpServersOutgoingQueueSize.name: bwXSTcpServersOutgoingQueueSize
bwXSTcpServersOutgoingQueueSize.description: This counter represents the number of bytes in the outgoing queue.

bwXSTcpServersIncomingQueueSize.name: bwXSTcpServersIncomingQueueSize
bwXSTcpServersIncomingQueueSize.description: This counter represents the number of bytes in the incoming queue.

bwXSTcpServersNbBytesSentSecure.name: bwXSTcpServersNbBytesSentSecure
bwXSTcpServersNbBytesSentSecure.description: This counter represents the number of bytes sent by the TCP server over secure connections.

bwXSTcpServersNbBytesReceivedSecure.name: bwXSTcpServersNbBytesReceivedSecure
bwXSTcpServersNbBytesReceivedSecure.description: This counter represents the number of bytes received by the TCP server over secure connections.

bwSOAPMaxSessions.name: bwSOAPMaxSessions
bwSOAPMaxSessions.description: Maximum number of incoming SOAP sessions simultaneously active since the system was started.

bwSOAPAvgSessions.name: bwSOAPAvgSessions
bwSOAPAvgSessions.description: Average number of incoming SOAP sessions simultaneously active, based on a rolling average over the last 100 sessions.

bwSOAPMaxThreads.name: bwSOAPMaxThreads
bwSOAPMaxThreads.description: This gauge measures the maximum percentage of SOAP processing threads simultaneously active since the system was started.

bwSOAPAvgThreads.name: bwSOAPAvgThreads
bwSOAPAvgThreads.description: Average percentage of SOAP threads simultaneously active, based on a rolling average over the last 100 sessions.

bwSOAPMaxServiceTime.name: bwSOAPMaxServiceTime
bwSOAPMaxServiceTime.description: Maximum time in milliseconds required to process an incoming SOAP request, since the system was started.

bwSOAPAvgServiceTime.name: bwSOAPAvgServiceTime
bwSOAPAvgServiceTime.description: Average time in milliseconds required to process an incoming SOAP request, based on a rolling average over the last 100 requests.

bwSOAPNumDroppedRequests.name: bwSOAPNumDroppedRequests
bwSOAPNumDroppedRequests.description: Number of SOAP server requests dropped because the number of SOAP threads was too low.

bwSmppSubmitSMRequestsSent.name: bwSmppSubmitSMRequestsSent
bwSmppSubmitSMRequestsSent.description: Number of outgoing SMPP submit_sm requests sent.

bwSmppSubmitSMResponseTimeout.name: bwSmppSubmitSMResponseTimeout
bwSmppSubmitSMResponseTimeout.description: Number of submit_sm requests timeouts detected.

bwCPEDeviceStatsTable.name: bwCPEDeviceStatsTable
bwCPEDeviceStatsTable.description: This table contains counters for the managed CPE devices management.

bwCPEDeviceStatsEntry.name: bwCPEDeviceStatsEntry
bwCPEDeviceStatsEntry.description: Definition of the entries for bwCPEDeviceStatsTable.

bwCPEDeviceStatsIndex.name: bwCPEDeviceStatsIndex
bwCPEDeviceStatsIndex.description: This integer represents a CPE device index in the table

bwCPEDeviceName.name: bwCPEDeviceName
bwCPEDeviceName.description: This string represents CPE device name

bwCPEDeviceReset.name: bwCPEDeviceReset
bwCPEDeviceReset.description: Number of time the Customer Premise Equipment has been reset. The CPE device is a subscriber IP Phone that can be reset/reloaded via the web portal or CLI. You must have administrative privileges to reset the phone.

bwCPEDeviceFileRebuilt.name: bwCPEDeviceFileRebuilt
bwCPEDeviceFileRebuilt.description: Number of time the Customer Premise Equipment has had its configuration file regenerated, the file can be regenerated in a number of ways, for example but not limited to - subscriber specific attribute has changed, a new line has been added to the device.

bwCPEDeviceFileGet.name: bwCPEDeviceFileGet
bwCPEDeviceFileGet.description: Number of time the Application Server retrieves a device file from the file repository, one counter per device.

bwCPEDeviceFileDelete.name: bwCPEDeviceFileDelete
bwCPEDeviceFileDelete.description: Number of time the Application Server deletes a device file from the file repository, one counter per device.

bwCPEDeviceFilePut.name: bwCPEDeviceFilePut
bwCPEDeviceFilePut.description: Number of time the Application Server saves a device file in the file repository, one counter per device.

bwCallpNetworkOriginationAttempts.name: bwCallpNetworkOriginationAttempts
bwCallpNetworkOriginationAttempts.description: This count indicates the total number of originations from the network.

bwCallpNetworkTerminationAttempts.name: bwCallpNetworkTerminationAttempts
bwCallpNetworkTerminationAttempts.description: This count indicates the total number of termination attempts to the network.

bwCallpNetworkTerminationsAnswered.name: bwCallpNetworkTerminationsAnswered
bwCallpNetworkTerminationsAnswered.description: This count indicates the total number of termination attempts to the network answered.

bwCallpUserOriginationAttempts.name: bwCallpUserOriginationAttempts
bwCallpUserOriginationAttempts.description: This counts indicates the total number of origination attempts from the access network(BroadWorks user/virtual user).

bwCallpUserTerminationAttempts.name: bwCallpUserTerminationAttempts
bwCallpUserTerminationAttempts.description: This counts indicates the total number of termination attempts to the access network(BroadWorks user/virtual user).

bwCallpUserTerminationsAnswered.name: bwCallpUserTerminationsAnswered
bwCallpUserTerminationsAnswered.description: This counts indicates the total number of termination attempts to the access network answered.

bwCallpEmergencyCallAttempts.name: bwCallpEmergencyCallAttempts
bwCallpEmergencyCallAttempts.description: This counter represents the number of Emergency call originations made by user's of the system

bwCallpEmergencyCallAlarms.name: bwCallpEmergencyCallAlarms
bwCallpEmergencyCallAlarms.description: The counter represents the number of times an alarm is generated for an emergency call routing failure

bwCallpSPTable.name: bwCallpSPTable
bwCallpSPTable.description: This table contains the counters for CallP measurements for service providers

bwCallpActiveCalls.name: bwCallpActiveCalls
bwCallpActiveCalls.description: This counts indicates the total number of active session. An active session is define as an active originating session. Any call that needs to perform a lookup in a NetworkServer/LocationServer will be counted as 2 calls, once for each call leg.

bwCallpGroupTable.name: bwCallpGroupTable
bwCallpGroupTable.description: This table contains the counters for CallP measurements for groups

bwCallpCallsPerSecond.name: bwCallpCallsPerSecond
bwCallpCallsPerSecond.description: This gauge measures the rate at which network origination attempts and user origination attempts occur. It uses the timestamps of up to the last 100 network origination attempts and user origination attempts in calculating the rate. The criteria for capturing such attempts is the same as that for pegging the bwCallPNetworkOriginationAttempts and bwCallPUserOriginationAttempts PM's.

bwCallpMaximumNumberofSimCallsExceeded.name: bwCallpMaximumNumberofSimCallsExceeded
bwCallpMaximumNumberofSimCallsExceeded.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum number of simultaneous calls for a user is exceeded.

bwCallpMaximumCallTimeforAnsweredCallsEx.name: bwCallpMaximumCallTimeforAnsweredCallsExceeded
bwCallpMaximumCallTimeforAnsweredCallsEx.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum call time for answered calls is exceeded.

bwCallpMaximumCallTimeforUnansweredCalls.name: bwCallpMaximumCallTimeforUnansweredCallsExceeded
bwCallpMaximumCallTimeforUnansweredCalls.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum call time for unanswered calls is exceeded.

bwCallpActiveCallsAsPercentOfLicense.name: bwCallpActiveCallsAsPercentOfLicense
bwCallpActiveCallsAsPercentOfLicense.description: This gauge reports the number of active calls as a percentage of the maximum concurrent calls licensed value. If the concurrent calls licensed value is unlimited, the gauge is zero.

bwCallpMaximumNumberofSimVideoCallsExcee.name: bwCallpMaximumNumberofSimVideoCallsExceeded
bwCallpMaximumNumberofSimVideoCallsExcee.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum number of simultaneous video calls for a user is exceeded.

bwCallpMediaTypeNotSupported.name: bwCallpMediaTypeNotSupported
bwCallpMediaTypeNotSupported.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the media type (codec) has not been supported for a user.

bwCallpRemoteOfficeEmergencyCallsBlocked.name: bwCallpRemoteOfficeEmergencyCallsBlocked
bwCallpRemoteOfficeEmergencyCallsBlocked.description: This is the number of times an emergency call origination attempt from a network location (i.e. remote office or BroadWorks anywhere) has been blocked.

bwCallpSPEntry.name: bwCallpSPEntry
bwCallpSPEntry.description: This row contains the counters for CallP measurements for a service provider

bwCallpSPIndex.name: bwCallpSPIndex
bwCallpSPIndex.description: This integer represents the a service provider index in the system

bwCallpSPID.name: bwCallpSPID
bwCallpSPID.description: This string represents a service provider ID

bwCallpSPUserOriginationAttempts.name: bwCallpSPUserOriginationAttempts
bwCallpSPUserOriginationAttempts.description: This counts indicates the total number of origination attempts from the access network(BroadWorks user/virtual user) for a service provider

bwCallpSPUserTerminationAttempts.name: bwCallpSPUserTerminationAttempts
bwCallpSPUserTerminationAttempts.description: This counts indicates the total number of termination attempts to the access network(BroadWorks user/virtual user) for a service provider

bwCallpSPUserTerminationsAnswered.name: bwCallpSPUserTerminationsAnswered
bwCallpSPUserTerminationsAnswered.description: This counts indicates the total number of termination attempts to the access network answered for a service provider

bwCallpSPEmergencyCallAttempts.name: bwCallpSPEmergencyCallAttempts
bwCallpSPEmergencyCallAttempts.description: This counter represents the number of Emergency call originations made by Broadworks users for a service provider

bwCallpSPMaximumNumberofSimCallsExceeded.name: bwCallpSPMaximumNumberofSimCallsExceeded
bwCallpSPMaximumNumberofSimCallsExceeded.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum number of simultaneous calls for a user is exceeded for a service provider.

bwCallpSPMaximumCallTimeforAnsweredCalls.name: bwCallpSPMaximumCallTimeforAnsweredCallsExceeded
bwCallpSPMaximumCallTimeforAnsweredCalls.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum call time for answered calls is exceeded for a service provider.

bwCallpSPMaximumCallTimeforUnansweredCal.name: bwCallpSPMaximumCallTimeforUnansweredCallsExceeded
bwCallpSPMaximumCallTimeforUnansweredCal.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum call time for unanswered calls is exceeded for a service provider.

bwCallpSPMaximumNumberofSimVideoCallsExc.name: bwCallpSPMaximumNumberofSimVideoCallsExceeded
bwCallpSPMaximumNumberofSimVideoCallsExc.description: The counter reflects the number of times that the maximum number of simultaneous video calls for a user is exceeded.

bwCallpSPMediaTypeNotSupported.name: bwCallpSPMediaTypeNotSupported
bwCallpSPMediaTypeNotSupported.description: The counter reflects the number of times that the media type (codec) within a service provider has not been supported for a user.

bwCallpGroupEntry.name: bwCallpGroupEntry
bwCallpGroupEntry.description: This row contains the counters for CallP measurements for a group

bwCallpGroupIndex.name: bwCallpGroupIndex
bwCallpGroupIndex.description: This integer represents the a group index in the system

bwCallpGroupID.name: bwCallpGroupID
bwCallpGroupID.description: This string represents a group ID

bwCallpGroupUserOriginationAttempts.name: bwCallpGroupUserOriginationAttempts
bwCallpGroupUserOriginationAttempts.description: This counts indicates the total number of origination attempts from the access network(BroadWorks user/virtual user) for a group

bwCallpGroupUserTerminationAttempts.name: bwCallpGroupUserTerminationAttempts
bwCallpGroupUserTerminationAttempts.description: This counts indicates the total number of termination attempts to the access network(BroadWorks user/virtual user) for a group

bwCallpGroupUserTerminationsAnswered.name: bwCallpGroupUserTerminationsAnswered
bwCallpGroupUserTerminationsAnswered.description: This counts indicates the total number of termination attempts to the access network answered for a group

bwCallpGroupEmergencyCallAttempts.name: bwCallpGroupEmergencyCallAttempts
bwCallpGroupEmergencyCallAttempts.description: This counter represents the number of Emergency call originations made by Broadworks users for a group

bwCallpGroupMaximumNumberofSimCallsExcee.name: bwCallpGroupMaximumNumberofSimCallsExceeded
bwCallpGroupMaximumNumberofSimCallsExcee.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum number of simultaneous calls for a user is exceeded for a group.

bwCallpGroupMaximumCallTimeforAnsweredCa.name: bwCallpGroupMaximumCallTimeforAnsweredCallsExceeded
bwCallpGroupMaximumCallTimeforAnsweredCa.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum call time for answered calls is exceeded for a group.

bwCallpGroupMaximumCallTimeforUnanswered.name: bwCallpGroupMaximumCallTimeforUnansweredCallsExceeded
bwCallpGroupMaximumCallTimeforUnanswered.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum call time for unanswered calls is exceeded for a group.

bwCallpGroupMaximumNumberofSimVideoCalls.name: bwCallpGroupMaximumNumberofSimVideoCallsExceeded
bwCallpGroupMaximumNumberofSimVideoCalls.description: This counter reflects the number of times that the maximum number of simultaneous video calls for a user is exceeded.

bwCallpGroupMediaTypeNotSupported.name: bwCallpGroupMediaTypeNotSupported
bwCallpGroupMediaTypeNotSupported.description: This counter reflects the number of times that a call is rejected because the media type was not valid for a user.

bwSMTPTotalPrimaryEmailSendAttempts.name: bwSMTPTotalPrimaryEmailSendAttempts
bwSMTPTotalPrimaryEmailSendAttempts.description: This counter reflects the total number of message send attempted on the primary SMTP server.

bwSMTPTotalSecondaryEmailSendAttempts.name: bwSMTPTotalSecondaryEmailSendAttempts
bwSMTPTotalSecondaryEmailSendAttempts.description: This counter reflects the total number of message send attempted on the secondary SMTP server.

bwSipStatsSetupSignalDelay.name: bwSipStatsSetupSignalDelay
bwSipStatsSetupSignalDelay.description: This gauge is applicable to SIP originated calls. It measures the average time (in milliseconds) it takes between the receipt of an INVITE message for the origination of a new call and the transmission of an INVITE (Sip terminator), RQNT (MGCP terminator with in-band ringback), or CRCX (MGCP terminator without in-band ringback) to the primary device of the original called party (in the case of intra-group call) or to the network element of the original called party (in the case of a call to the PSTN). Delays incurred by a query to an external element (e.g. - dip to the Network Server, CNAME query, any external database interaction incurred by CPL scripting) are part of the measurement. This measurement is intended to reflect the elapsed delay between receipt of the call setup signal from the caller and transmission of the call setup signal to the called party

bwSipStatsMinSetupSignalDelay.name: bwSipStatsMinSetupSignalDelay
bwSipStatsMinSetupSignalDelay.description: This measures the shortest SIP setup-signal delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared

bwSipStatsMaxSetupSignalDelay.name: bwSipStatsMaxSetupSignalDelay
bwSipStatsMaxSetupSignalDelay.description: This measures the longest SIP setup-signal delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared

bwSipStatsAnswerSignalDelay.name: bwSipStatsAnswerSignalDelay
bwSipStatsAnswerSignalDelay.description: This gauge measures the average time (in milliseconds) between the receipt of a 200 OK message indicating answer or a NTFY off-hook indicating answer and the transmission of a 200 OK indicating answer to the originator. This measurement is intended to reflect internal queuing, scheduling, and processing delays. This gauge is applicable to only the SIP originated calls for which the setup-signal delay is measured. Answer signal delay is not measured when the call has been forwarded, redirected, or when the call has encountered route advancing

bwSipStatsMinAnswerSignalDelay.name: bwSipStatsMinAnswerSignalDelay
bwSipStatsMinAnswerSignalDelay.description: This measures the shortest SIP answer-signal delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared

bwSipStatsMaxAnswerSignalDelay.name: bwSipStatsMaxAnswerSignalDelay
bwSipStatsMaxAnswerSignalDelay.description: This measures the longest SIP answer-signal delay sampled since the system was started or since this measurement was cleared

bwSipStatsRegistrationsPerMinute.name: bwSipStatsRegistrationsPerMinute
bwSipStatsRegistrationsPerMinute.description: This gauge measures the rate at which the Application Server receives SIP REGISTER messages. It uses the timestamps of up to the last 100 registrations received in calculating the rate

bwSipStatsMsgRetryPercentageToOther.name: bwSipStatsMsgRetryPercentageToOther
bwSipStatsMsgRetryPercentageToOther.description: This gauge measures the percentage of SIP requests and reliable responses sent (to nodes other than those covered by bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeTable) due to retry. Of up to the last 100 requests and reliable responses sent, this gauge calculates the percentage sent due to retransmission (i.e. - gauge = (SIP request retransmissions + SIP reliable response retransmissions) / (SIP request initial transmissions + SIP request retransmissions + SIP reliable response initial transmissions + SIP reliable response retransmissions)

bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeTable.name: bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeTable
bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeTable.description: This gauge table consists of a bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNEEntry per Network Element address. A Network Element can be a Network Server, Media Server, a Network Gateway, etc - anything but an access device.

bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeEntry.name: bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeEntry
bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeEntry.description: This row contains information on a particular Network Element

bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeID.name: bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeID
bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeID.description: This integer represents the unique index of a Network Element

bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeAddr.name: bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeAddr
bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNeAddr.description: This string represents a Network Element address

bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNePercentage.name: bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNePercentage
bwSipStatsMsgRetryToNePercentage.description: The gauge measures for that particular Network Element the percentage of SIP requests and reliable responses sent due to retry. Of up to the last 100 requests and reliable responses sent to a particular NetworkElement address, this gauge calculates the percentage sent due to retransmission (i.e. - gauge = (SIP request retransmissions + SIP reliable response retransmissions) / (SIP request initial transmissions + SIP request retransmissions + SIP reliable response initial transmissions + SIP reliable response retransmissions).
